---
  import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
  import FullWidthHero from '../components/FullWidthHero.astro'
  import CallToAction from '../components/CallToAction.astro'
---
<Base>
  <FullWidthHero></FullWidthHero>
  <!-- ABOUT ME -->
  <div class="about-me">
    <div class="left-col">
      <img
        alt=""
        class="profile-picture"
        src="~/assets/images/richard-profile.png"
      />
      <div class="cta-take-test-btn">
        <p class="btn-text">Take the test</p>
      </div>
      <p class="i-work-with">I work with...</p>
      <div class="work-with-list">
        <div class="flex-wrapper-one">
          <p class="elders-65-adults-suffering-from-c">
            Elders (65 &#43;)<br />
            <br />
            Adults suffering from...<br />
            <br />
            Caretakers and Families<br />
          </p>
          <img
            alt=""
            class="checkmark-2-1"
            src="~/assets/images/checkmark.svg"
          />
        </div>
        <img
          alt=""
          class="checkmark-2-1-two"
          src="~/assets/images/checkmark.svg"
        /><img
          alt=""
          class="checkmark-2-2"
          src="~/assets/images/checkmark.svg"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="left-col">
      <p class="meet-richard-breuner">Meet Richard Breuner</p>
      <div class="about-me-text">
        <p class="im-a-native-californian-but-have-lived">
          I’m a native Californian but have lived in Reno for the last 8
          years. Following a traditional life raising a family and a career in
          real estate, I decided to go back to school to study psychology at
          UNR. I landed in the discipline of Behavior Analysis which prepared
          me to look at behavior with a scientific perspective. In addition to
          my Master’s degree in Psychology, I am a Board Certified Behavior
          Analyst (BCBA), and a licensed Behavior Analyst in Nevada and an
          Aging in Place Specialist.
        </p>
        <p class="i-work-with-young-adults-adults-and-esp">
          I work with young adults, adults and especially aging individuals
          and their loved ones who are experiencing or concerned with
          behavioral challenges and aging independently and well. Regardless
          of age, I work I assess one’s lifestyle domains and activities of
          daily living to best arrange for ongoing independence, satisfaction
          and happiness. These experiences call for routine functional
          analysis, cognitive assessment and the preparation of behavioral
          support plans.
        </p>
        <p class="with-few-exceptions-anything-someone-do">
          With few exceptions, anything someone does, says or even thinks has
          function. It is willful. When suffering, our behavior still has
          function but it also produces uncomfortable consequences.
        </p>
        <p class="we-may-appear-disabled-but-our-will-to-c">
          We may appear disabled but our will to contact reinforcement,
          success and safety is not. Solutions present when we ask what new
          conditions we may arrange to get what we desire but without painful
          consequences.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <!-- HELPFUL INFO Component -->
  <div class="helpful-info">
    <div class="location-two">
      <p class="location">Location</p>
      <p class="bend-oregon-reno-nevada">
        Bend, OREGON<br />
        Reno, NEVADA
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="qualifications-two">
      <p class="qualifications">Qualifications</p>
      <p class="university-of-reno-nevada-years-in-prac">
        University of Reno, NEVADA<br />
        Years in Practice: 3 years
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="location-two">
      <p class="accepted-payment-methods">Accepted Payment Methods</p>
      <p class="fee-for-service-cash-check-visa-mc-o">
        Fee for service; cash, check, Visa, MC or mobile app
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <CallToAction></CallToAction>÷
</Base>

